Usage: assignBump [-help] [-constraint_file <string>]
                  [-exclude_region <llx lly urx ury ...>]
                  [-maxDistance <integer>] [-multiBumpToMultiPad] [{[-pgnet <pgnetList> | -exclude_pgnet <exclude_pgnetList>] [-pginst <pginstList>]} [-pgonly ]] [{-area <llx lly urx ury> | -selected }]

-help                                  # Prints out the command usage
-area <llx lly urx ury>                # assign bump in the specified area
                                       # (box, optional)
-constraint_file <string>              # path name to the file to load bump
                                       # assignment constraints from
                                       # (string, optional)
-exclude_pgnet <exclude_pgnetList>     # PG net not to assign
                                       # ((net)*, optional)
-exclude_region <llx lly urx ury ...>  # assign bump out of the specified area
                                       # (double, optional)
-maxDistance <integer>                 # the maximum distance, in microns,to
                                       # look for bump connection (int, optional)
-multiBumpToMultiPad                   # multiple bump to assign multiple pad
                                       # (bool, optional)
-pginst <pginstList>                   # PG insts to assign ((inst)+, optional)
-pgnet <pgnetList>                     # PG net to assign ((net)+, optional)
-pgonly                                # only PG net to assign (bool, optional)
-selected                              # assign selected pads/bumps
                                       # (bool, optional)